OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1782134325
OL,3,CPeople must stand united in condemning
OL,4,CEdinburgh attacks, says John Swinney
OL,6,F"My thoughts are with all who have
OL,7,Fbeen impacted ` the victims but also
OL,8,Fthe communities who are understandably
OL,9,Fanxious by what happened."
OL,11,FSwinney said people must "stand united
OL,12,Fin utter condemnation" of the
OL,13,F"heinous" attacks that took place in
OL,14,FEdinburgh.
OL,16,F"Anti-Muslim hatred is abhorrent, and
OL,17,Fwe must not allow recent attempts to
OL,18,Fstoke fear to divide us," he added.
