OL,3,CPeople must stand united in condemning
OL,4,CEdinburgh attacks, says John Swinney
OL,6,F"Everyone who lives in Scotland `
OL,7,Fthose that were born here and those
OL,8,Fthat have decided to make Scotland
OL,9,Ftheir home ` epitomise Scotland's
OL,10,Fvalues of hope, tolerance and
OL,11,Fsolidarity.
OL,13,F"These are values that must be
OL,14,Fcherished, nurtured and protected. We
OL,15,Fmust all come together to ensure that.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
