OL,3,CPeople must stand united in condemning
OL,4,CEdinburgh attacks, says John Swinney
OL,6,F"I am grateful to Police Scotland for
OL,7,Fthe continued work they are
OL,8,Fundertaking to ensure communities feel
OL,9,Fsafe and supported. I want to reassure
OL,10,Fcommunities that my government will
OL,11,Flead from the front in tackling all
OL,12,Fforms of violence, division and
OL,13,Fprejudice."
OL,15,FOn Saturday, the Prime Minister posted
OL,16,Fon X, linking to an image of a bare-
OL,17,Fchested man carrying a large weapon,
OL,18,Fsaying: "Absolutely appalling. No one
OL,19,Fshould face violence on our streets.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@KO]zD@IOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
